  "verification_notes": "Tony Skinn completed his 3rd season as head coach. Patriots finished 23-10 (11-7 A-10). Started season 18-1 (6-0 A-10), best start in program history. Lost in A-10 Tournament Second Round to St. Bonaventure; accepted NIT bid and lost First Round to Liberty. Did NOT make NCAA Tournament. Skinn signed a contract extension during/after the 2025-26 season per NBC Sports. Confirmed 2026-27 incoming transfers (per gomason.com): Efeosa Oliogu-Elabor (Butler), Emmett Adair (Loyola MD), Michael Marcus Jr. (Appalachian State). Tony Skinn's career record not separately verified — left null. Athletic director Marvin Lewis confirmed. EagleBank Arena basketball capacity is 7,860 (overall capacity 10,000); new Basketball and Academic Performance Center scheduled to open early 2027. Isaiah Skinn is the head coach's son. Roster shown is 2025-26 season-end. 2026-27 schedule TBD.",
